---
import { Button } from "#ui/button";
import { SectionWrapper } from "#components/wrappers/section-wrapper";
import { ImageWithAnnotation } from "#ui/image-annotation";
import { TargetPageWrapper } from "#components/wrappers/target-page-wrapper";
import Layout from "#layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Landing"
  description="What is a landing page? Instant will explain!"
>
  <div class="flex flex-col w-full h-full items-center min-h-screen pt-36 lg:pt-24">
    <TargetPageWrapper
      client:load
      title="Landing"
      description="this is a separate page created for marketing or advertising purposes to increase conversions."
      anchor="landing-information"
      backgroundColor="bg-blue-800"
    />
    <div id="landing-information" class="flex flex-col wrapper">
      <SectionWrapper
        client:load
        id="landing-pluses"
        title="Landing page advantages"
      >
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 *:text-md lg:*:text-lg *:text-white">
          <li>
            <p>- simple lead generation</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>- collecting client data</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>- improving SEO performance</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>- great opportunity to promote new products</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>- streamlined decision-making process</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </SectionWrapper>
      <SectionWrapper
        client:load
        id="landing-how-to-work"
        title="How does the landing page work?"
      >
        <div
          class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-4 *:text-md lg:*:text-lg *:text-white"
        >
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-6">
            <p>
              Landing works extremely simply. After clicking a link, the user is
              taken to a landing page that showcases a special offer or
              describes a specific product.
            </p>
            <p>
              The main element of the landing page is a clear CTA, quality
              image, and text that encourages people to fill out a subscription
              form. To access the special offer, the user needs to leave their
              details â€” thus becoming a lead.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-y-1">
              <p>The key components of a landing page are:</p>
              <p>- captivating headline</p>
              <p>- relevant text</p>
              <p>- attention-grabbing images</p>
              <p>- features and benefits</p>
              <p>- subscription form</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ImageWithAnnotation
            propSrc="/images/landing-duolingo.png"
            propAlt="Duo example"
            annotation="Example of a landing page using Duolingo"
          />
        </div>
      </SectionWrapper>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper w-fit mb-12">
      <a href="/#contacts">
        <Button client:load>
          <p class="text-lg text-white font-medium">Contact Us</p>
        </Button>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
